Enteroviral case management - China (Hong Kong) 980713202444
Enterovirus 71 epidemic, children - China (Hong Kong) 980701201715
Date: Wed, 15 Jul 1998 00:48:52 +0800
Source: Hong Kong Special Administrative Region Dept. of Health
Via: Dr.M.Vadivale <vale@pop.jaring.my>

[The following message is re-posted to correct formatting errors that
resulted in movement of the title line out of the appropriate field. My
apologies for the inconvenience. - Mod.ES
Statistics on hand-foot-mouth (HFM) disease.
Week ending/ Number of HFM disease reported Sentinel surveillance
centres*/ Hospital inpatients without complication/ with complication(s)#
20 Jun 98 / 72 / NA / NA
27 Jun 98 / 110 / 16 / 0
04 Jul 98 / 173 / 42 / 0
* 63 General Outpatient Clinics of Department of Health and 17 general
practitioners
#Complication refers to aseptic meningitis, encephalitis (brain infection),
myocarditis (heart infection), acute flaccid paralysis, rapidly
deteriorating clinical course and death
As at 6 July 1998, there are 1 confirmed and 6 suspected cases of
enterovirus 71 infections. All presented with mild symptoms and made full
recovery.
